  "title": "CAPACITY MANAGEMENT SHIPPING OFFICER/EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>General Area of Responsibility</strong></u></p>\n<p>Ensure optimization of vessels for the overall Network and at the same time minimizing all relevant cost.</p>\n<p>Monitoring slot utilization of vessel against allocation and capacity.</p>\n<p><strong>Specific Areas of Responsibility</strong></p>\n<p>1. Daily Reports to Liners in Singapore and Geneva HQ</p>\n<p>- <strong>Daily Bookings</strong></p>\n<p>Ensure the accuracy of agent’s forecast/final loading through system (I-space)</p>\n<p>Monitor allocation/diversion instructions by the respective line managers and ensure agents follow up and update in the system.</p>\n<p>- Assist Network Operations &amp; Line Manager to simulate vessel’s connections/utilization during contingency/omission plans.</p>\n<p>- <strong>Daily Executive Summary</strong></p>\n<p>Liaise with agency offices (POL) pertaining to market trend- increase/decrease in cargoes projections and report to line managers.</p>\n<p>- <strong>Daily Diagram</strong></p>\n<p>- Summary of vessel utilization for all strings. This will facilitate Line Manager’s decisions on cargoes diversions between services and rate actions, etc.</p>\n<p>- Review overall network utilization and propose for the necessary diversion &amp; connections plans to optimize each string.</p>\n<p>2. Monitoring cargoes connections and instructing transhipment ports (6 main T/S ports: <em><strong>NBO/SHA/YTN/PUS/SIN/VUT</strong></em>) of planned cargoes nominations base on allocation assigned by line managers.</p>\n<p>- Planned for cargoes diversions and rollovers by instructing transhipment POLs</p>\n<p>- Review possible miss connections and advancement of cargoes to optimize utilization of the vessels.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Other General Duties</strong></u></p>\n<p>1. Uploading of bay-plans in CAMS</p>\n<p>2. Updating iSpace as necessary</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Candidate Requirement</strong></p>\n<p>· Degree/Diploma holder, preferably in Maritime Transportation or Nautical Studies.</p>\n<p>· Minimum 2 years working experience in container shipping industry.</p>\n<p>· Independent and able to work under pressure to meet deadlines.</p>\n<p>· Able to work long hours, on weekends and public holidays when required.</p>\n<p>· Good interpersonal, communication and time management skills.</p>\n<p>· Proficient in Microsoft Office applications.</p>\n<p>· Working knowledge of CASP is essential but not necessary.</p>\n<p>· Believe in team-driven culture.</p>\n<p>The ability to speak various languages is also welcome</p>",
